#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.103"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.103:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: sambodhivaggo (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.103:0.2"
msgid "11. Sambodhavagga"
msgstr "11. Awakening"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.103:0.3"
msgid "103. Pubbevasambodhasutta"
msgstr "103. Before Awakening"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.259"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.103:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on "
"awakening—I thought:"

msgctxt "an3.103:1.2"
msgid "‘ko nu kho loke assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘What’s the gratification in the world? What’s the drawback? What’s the "
"escape?’"

msgctxt "an3.103:1.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

#. VAR: lokaṃ → loke (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.4"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho lokaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ loke assādo."
msgstr ""
"‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from the world: this is its "
"gratification."

#. VAR: loko → loke (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.5"
msgid "Yaṃ loko anicco dukkho vipariṇāmadhammo, ayaṃ loke ādīnavo."
msgstr ""
"That the world is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its "
"drawback."

#. VAR: loke nissaraṇan’ti → lokanissaraṇaṃ (aṭṭha.)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.6"
msgid "Yo loke chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ loke nissaraṇan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Removing and giving up desire and greed for the world: this is its escape.’"

#. VAR: abhisambuddho’ti → abhisambuddho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.7"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ lokassa assādañca assādato ādīnavañca "
"ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"As long as I didn’t truly understand the world’s gratification, drawback, "
"and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme "
"perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans."

#. VAR: khvāhaṃ → kho ahaṃ (bj, pts1) | khohaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.8"
msgid ""
"Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, evaṃ lokassa assādañca assādato ādīnavañca "
"ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya "
"sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"But when I did truly understand the world’s gratification, drawback, and "
"escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect "
"awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population "
"with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans."

msgctxt "an3.103:1.9"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:"
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me:"

#. VAR: vimutti → cetovimutti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.103:1.10"
msgid "‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more "
"future lives.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.103:1.11"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
